properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued February 9 at 3:07PM EST until February 10 at 6:00PM EST by NWS Mount Holly NJ
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest winds 15 to 20 knots with gusts up to 30
knots and seas 4 to 6 feet are expected.

* WHERE...The Atlantic coastal waters of Delaware and New Jersey.

* WHEN...From midnight tonight until 6:00 PM Monday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
Inexperienced mariners, especially those operating a small
vessel, should avoid navigating in hazardous conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO 6 PM EST MONDAY
